#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:4
#, no-c-format
msgid "Command"
msgstr "आदेश"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &partman; commands are what <link linkend=\"glossary-job\">jobs</link> "
"are made up of. These are very low level steps being taken, often executed "
"by an external tool, and only visible in the detailed progress report."
msgstr ""
"In &amp;partman; आदेशाः किम्<link linkend=\"glossary-job\"> कार्याणि</link> "
"निर्मिताः भवन्ति। एते अत्यल्पस्तरस्य पदानि क्रियन्ते, प्रायः बाह्यसाधनेन निष्पादितानि, "
"विस्तृतप्रगतिप्रतिवेदने एव दृश्यन्ते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:9
#, no-c-format
msgid "The user normally does not have to bother with commands at all."
msgstr "सामान्यतया उपयोक्त्रेण आदेशैः सर्वथा कष्टं न कर्तव्यम् ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:11
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:18
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cylinder"
msgstr "सिलिण्डर"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:20
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. "
"Some operating systems and many disk tools require <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partition\">partitions</link> to begin and end on a cylinder. &partman; "
"therefore automatically snaps partitions to cylinder boundaries when "
"changing their start or end."
msgstr ""
"विभक्तुं प्रयुक्तं एककं क<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> . केचन "
"प्रचालनतन्त्राणि, बहवः डिस्कसाधनाः च आवश्यकाः सन्ति<link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> सिलिण्डरे आरम्भं समाप्तुं च । &amp;partman; अतः स्वयमेव "
"विभाजनं सिलिण्डरसीमासु स्नैप करोति यदा तेषां आरम्भं वा अन्तं वा परिवर्तयति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:22
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:29
#, no-c-format
msgid "Cylinder Size"
msgstr "सिलिण्डर आकार"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:31
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sectors</link> per <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-cylinder\">cylinder</link> on a <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"device\">device</link>. Calculated as the number of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"head\">heads</link> multiplied by the number of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"sector\">sectors</link> per track."
msgstr ""
"इति संख्या<link linkend=\"glossary-sector\"> क्षेत्रेषु</link> प्रति<link linkend="
"\"glossary-cylinder\"> सिलिण्डर</link> on a<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> "
"उपकरणम्‌</link> . सङ्ख्या इति गणितम्<link linkend=\"glossary-head\"> शिरः</link> "
"सङ्ख्यायाः गुणितः<link linkend=\"glossary-sector\"> क्षेत्रेषु</link> प्रति पटलम्।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:38
#, no-c-format
msgid "Device"
msgstr "उपकरणम्‌"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:40
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A physical disk device. Physical disk devices are divided into logical "
"sections called <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partitions</link> with "
"the use of <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition tables</link>."
msgstr ""
"एकं भौतिकं डिस्कयन्त्रम् । भौतिक-डिस्क-यन्त्राणि तार्किक-खण्डेषु विभक्ताः भवन्ति, येषां "
"नाम<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> प्रयोगेन सह<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\"> विभाजनसारणीः</link> ."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid "Disk Label"
msgstr "डिस्क लेबल"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:49
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Another name for a <link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition "
"table</link> stemming from the SUN/BSD world."
msgstr ""
"अन्यत् नाम क<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\"> विभाजनसारणी</link> SUN/"
"BSD जगतः उद्भूतः।"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:54
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are easy to mix up, but a disk label has nothing to do with a <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">file system label</link>."
msgstr ""
"तेषां मिश्रणं सुलभं भवति, परन्तु डिस्कलेबलस्य a इत्यनेन सह किमपि सम्बन्धः नास्ति<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"> सञ्चिकातन्त्रलेबलम्</link> ."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:57
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"See <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_disklabel\">this Wikipedia "
"entry</ulink> for details on the name."
msgstr ""
"नामविवरणार्थं <ulink url=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/BSD_disklabel\">इयं "
"विकिपीडियाप्रविष्टिः</ulink> पश्यन्तु ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid "Extended Partition"
msgstr "विस्तारित विभाजन"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:69
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> that contains other "
"partitions. Extended partitions can only be <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primary partitions</link> themselves. Whether extended "
"partitions are available or not depends on the <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partitiontable\">partition table</link> type used. MS-DOS partition tables "
"allow one extended partition per <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</"
"link>."
msgstr ""
"एकः<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> यस्मिन् अन्ये विभाजनाः "
"सन्ति । विस्तारिताः विभाजनाः केवलं भवितुम् अर्हन्ति<link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\"> प्राथमिक विभाजन</link> तस्मान्। विस्तारिताः विभाजनाः उपलभ्यन्ते "
"वा न वा इति निर्भरं भवति<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\"> "
"विभाजनसारणी</link> प्रकारः प्रयुक्तः । MS-DOS विभाजनसारणीः प्रति एकं विस्तारितं "
"विभाजनं अनुमन्यन्ते<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> ."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"शब्दकोश-तार्किकविभाजनम्\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid "File System"
msgstr "सञ्चिकातन्त्रम्"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:80
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A file system defines how the storage of data (files with their metadata, "
"folders and their metadata, free space) is organized within a <link linkend="
"\"glossary-partition\">partition</link>. There are various different types "
"of file systems, some coming originally from the Unix/Linux world, some not. "
"Examples for commonly used file systems on Unix/Linux are Btrfs, ext4 and "
"XFS."
msgstr ""
"सञ्चिकातन्त्रं परिभाषयति यत् दत्तांशस्य भण्डारणं (तस्य मेटाडाटा सह सञ्चिकाः, पुटं तथा च तेषां "
"मेटाडाटा, मुक्तस्थानं) a<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> . "
"तत्र विविधाः भिन्नाः प्रकाराः सञ्चिकातन्त्राः सन्ति, केचन मूलतः Unix/Linux जगतः "
"आगच्छन्ति, केचन न । Unix/Linux इत्यत्र सामान्यतया प्रयुक्तानां सञ्चिकातन्त्राणां उदाहरणानि "
"सन्ति Btrfs, ext4 तथा XFS ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "File System Label"
msgstr "सञ्चिकातन्त्र लेबल"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:89
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A title of a file system. Some file systems (among them Btrfs, ext2/3/4, "
"FAT16/32 and NTFS) support setting a label for the file system so it can be "
"identified in tools like &partman; or other applications."
msgstr ""
"सञ्चिकातन्त्रस्य शीर्षकम् । केचन सञ्चिकातन्त्राणि (तेषु Btrfs, ext2/3/4, FAT16/32 तथा "
"NTFS) सञ्चिकातन्त्रस्य कृते लेबलं सेट् कर्तुं समर्थयन्ति येन &partman; अन्ये वा अनुप्रयोगाः।"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"They are easy to mix up, but a file system label has nothing to do with a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">disk label</link>."
msgstr ""
"तेषां मिश्रणं सुलभं भवति, परन्तु सञ्चिकातन्त्रलेबलस्य a इत्यनेन सह किमपि सम्बन्धः नास्ति<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\"> डिस्क लेबल</link> ."

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:101
#, no-c-format
msgid "Flag"
msgstr "ध्वजा"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:106
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>GPT</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>GPT</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:108
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A modern partition table format supported by most modern computers and "
"operating systems. It supports more than 4 <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"primarypartition\">primary partitions</link> unlike older MS-DOS partition "
"table."
msgstr ""
"अधिकांशैः आधुनिकसङ्गणकैः, प्रचालनतन्त्रैः च समर्थितं आधुनिकं विभाजनसारणीस्वरूपम् । इदं ४ तः "
"अधिकं समर्थयति<link linkend=\"glossary-primarypartition\"> प्राथमिक विभाजन</"
"link> प्राचीन MS-DOS विभाजनसारणीयाः विपरीतम् ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid "Head"
msgstr "शिरः"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:116
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>."
msgstr "विभक्तुं प्रयुक्तं एककं क<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> ."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:118
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-sector\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"शब्दकोश-क्षेत्र\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:125
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>Job</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>कार्य</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:127
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In &partman; a number of jobs is what <link linkend=\"glossary-operation"
"\">operations</link> are made up of. You normally do not have to bother with "
"jobs at all; it only becomes apparent when applying the list of pending "
"operations: &partman; will then show a progress dialog that is made up of "
"all operations and their jobs and show which operation and which job is "
"currently being executed."
msgstr ""
"In &amp;partman; कार्याणां संख्या किम् अस्ति<link linkend=\"glossary-operation\"> "
"संचालनम्</link> निर्मिताः भवन्ति। सामान्यतया भवद्भिः कार्यैः सर्वथा कष्टं न कर्तव्यम्; केवलं "
"लम्बितसञ्चालनसूचीं प्रयोक्तुं स्पष्टं भवति: &amp;partman; ततः एकं प्रगतिसंवादं दर्शयिष्यति यत् "
"सर्वैः कार्यैः तेषां कार्यैः च निर्मितं भवति तथा च दर्शयिष्यति यत् वर्तमानकाले कः कार्यः कः "
"कार्यः निष्पादितः भवति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:129
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-operation\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:136
#, no-c-format
msgid "Label"
msgstr "नामपत्र"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:138
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Either a <link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\">disk label</link> or a <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\">file system label</link>."
msgstr ""
"वा क<link linkend=\"glossary-disklabel\"> डिस्क लेबल</link> अथवा क<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"> सञ्चिकातन्त्रलेबलम्</link> ."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:140
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-disklabel\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-disklabel\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-filesystemlabel\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:147
#, no-c-format
msgid "Logical Partition"
msgstr "तार्किक विभाजन"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:149
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> inside an <link "
"linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition\">extended partition</link>."
msgstr ""
"एकः<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> अन्तः अण्<link linkend="
"\"glossary-extendedpartition\"> विस्तारितं विभाजनम्</link> ."

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:151
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"शब्दकोश-विस्तारितविभाजनम्\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:158
#, no-c-format
msgid "LUKS"
msgstr "विलास"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:160
#, no-c-format
msgid "Linux Unified Key Setup is the standard encryption format for Linux."
msgstr "Linux Unified Key Setup इति Linux कृते मानकगुप्तीकरणस्वरूपम् अस्ति ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "<glossterm>LVM</glossterm>"
msgstr "<glossterm>LVM</glossterm> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:168
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM is a system for managing logical partitions that is more flexible than "
"normal partitions. It consists of three main components:"
msgstr ""
"LVM इति तार्किकविभाजनानां प्रबन्धनार्थं प्रणाली अस्ति या सामान्यविभाजनानां अपेक्षया अधिकं "
"लचीलं भवति । अस्य मुख्यतया त्रयः घटकाः सन्ति-"

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:170
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM physical volumes are partitions on the disk whose space is managed by "
"LVM."
msgstr ""
"LVM भौतिक-आयतनानि डिस्क-मध्ये विभाजनानि सन्ति येषां स्थानं LVM द्वारा प्रबन्धितं भवति ।"

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:171
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM volume group is a collection of LVM physical volumes that can be "
"partitioned into logical partitions. It might be used to create file systems "
"spanning over multiple devices or to split encrypted <link linkend="
"\"glossary-luks\">LUKS</link> volume into smaller partitions."
msgstr ""
"LVM आयतनसमूहः LVM भौतिक आयतनानां संग्रहः अस्ति यत् तार्किकविभाजनेषु विभक्तुं शक्यते । "
"अनेकयन्त्राणां उपरि विस्तृतानि सञ्चिकातन्त्राणि निर्मातुं वा एन्क्रिप्टेड् विभक्तुं वा अस्य "
"उपयोगः भवितुं शक्नोति<link linkend=\"glossary-luks\"> लुक्स्</link> आयतनं लघुविभाजनेषु "
"।"

#. Tag: member
#: glossary.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"LVM logical volumes are similar to normal partitions except that they reside "
"on LVM volume group. Also, the location of LVM logical partitions does not "
"matter and they do not have to be physically contiguous. Therefore, "
"&partman; does not allow to move LVM logical volumes and displays the "
"remaining free space at the end of the device."
msgstr ""
"LVM तार्किक आयतनं सामान्यविभाजनानां सदृशं भवति केवलं यत् ते LVM आयतनसमूहे निवसन्ति । अपि "
"च, LVM तार्किकविभाजनस्य स्थानं महत्त्वपूर्णं नास्ति तथा च तेषां भौतिकरूपेण सङ्गतिः न "
"भवितुमर्हति । अतः &partman; LVM तार्किक आयतनं चालयितुं न अनुमन्यते तथा च यन्त्रस्य अन्ते "
"अवशिष्टं मुक्तस्थानं प्रदर्शयति ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:178
#, no-c-format
msgid "Operation"
msgstr "संचालन"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&partman; divides the work it does into operations, <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"job\">jobs</link> and <link linkend=\"glossary-command\">commands</link>."
msgstr ""
"&amp;partman; यत् कार्यं करोति तत् कार्याणि विभजति, .<link linkend=\"glossary-job"
"\"> कार्याणि</link> तथा<link linkend=\"glossary-command\"> आदेशाः</link> ."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:183
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operations are the most visible of the three. If you pick an action in the "
"graphical user interface, this will likely result in a new operation being "
"added to the list of pending operations. The idea behind that is: You will "
"most probably want to set up quite a number of steps to transform the "
"current state of your disk devices to the state you have in mind. Some of "
"these steps may take quite a long time to execute (like copying a large file "
"system or resizing a file system that is nearly full). To save you from "
"having to sit in front of your computer for a long time waiting for one step "
"to finish and then starting the next one, operations allow you to exactly "
"specify how the computer's devices should look like once everything is "
"finished, then let &partman; apply the operations and come back when it has "
"executed all of them."
msgstr ""
"त्रयाणां मध्ये कार्याणि सर्वाधिकं दृश्यन्ते । यदि भवान् चित्रात्मक-उपयोक्तृ-अन्तरफलके किमपि "
"क्रियां चिनोति तर्हि एतस्य परिणामः सम्भवतः लम्बित-क्रियाणां सूचीयां नूतनं कार्यं योजितं "
"भविष्यति । तस्य पृष्ठतः विचारः अस्ति यत्: भवान् अधिकतया स्वस्य डिस्क-यन्त्राणां वर्तमान-"
"स्थितिं भवतः मनसि स्थापिता अवस्थायां परिवर्तयितुं बहुधा पदानि स्थापयितुम् इच्छति । एतेषु "
"केषुचित् पदेषु निष्पादनार्थं बहुकालं यावत् समयः भवितुं शक्नोति (यथा बृहत् सञ्चिकातन्त्रस्य "
"प्रतिलिपिः अथवा प्रायः पूर्णस्य सञ्चिकातन्त्रस्य आकारं परिवर्तयितुं) । एकं पदं समाप्तं भवति "
"इति प्रतीक्ष्य सङ्गणकस्य पुरतः दीर्घकालं यावत् उपविश्य ततः परं पदं आरभ्यत इति रक्षितुं, "
"क्रियाः भवन्तं सम्यक् निर्दिष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति यत् एकवारं सर्वं समाप्तं जातं चेत् सङ्गणकस्य उपकरणानि "
"कथं दृश्यन्ते इति, ततः &partman इति ; क्रियाः प्रयोजयित्वा सर्वाणि निष्पादिते सति पुनः "
"आगच्छन्तु ।"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:186
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Operations are kept in a list of pending operations. As long as an operation "
"has not been applied it can still be <link linkend=\"menu-edit-undo\">taken "
"back easily</link> and nothing will have been modified."
msgstr ""
"परिचालनं लम्बितसञ्चालनस्य सूचीयां स्थापितं भवति । यावत् यावत् शल्यक्रिया न प्रयुक्ता तावत् "
"अद्यापि भवितुम् अर्हति<link linkend=\"menu-edit-undo\"> सहजतया पुनः गृहीतम्</link> "
"न च किमपि परिवर्तनं कृतं भविष्यति।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-job\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-command\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:195
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition"
msgstr "विभाजनम्"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A section of a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">hard disk device</link> "
"that can hold a <link linkend=\"glossary-filesystem\">file system</link> or "
"other partitions. Without at least one valid partition, a disk can not be "
"used."
msgstr ""
"एकः खण्डः क<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> हार्डडिस्कयन्त्रम्</link> यत् धारयितुं "
"शक्नोति क<link linkend=\"glossary-filesystem\"> सञ्चिकातन्त्रम्</link> अन्ये वा "
"विभाजनाः । न्यूनातिन्यूनम् एकं वैधविभाजनं विना डिस्कस्य उपयोगः कर्तुं न शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:199
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-device\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-partitiontable\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-device\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-partitiontable\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-primarypartition\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> इति <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:209
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition Flag"
msgstr "विभाजन ध्वज"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:211
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A marker for a <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link>. The "
"availability of these flags depends on the type of <link linkend=\"glossary-"
"partitiontable\">partition table</link> used."
msgstr ""
"क. कृते एकः चिह्नः<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> . एतेषां "
"ध्वजानां उपलब्धता प्रकारस्य आधारेण भवति<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\"> "
"विभाजनसारणी</link> प्रयुक्त।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:218
#, no-c-format
msgid "Partition Table"
msgstr "विभाजन सारणी"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A small section at the beginning of a <link linkend=\"glossary-device"
"\">device</link> used to store information about the layout of the device's "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partitions</link>. There are different "
"types of partition tables, each with their own limitations."
msgstr ""
"आदौ लघुखण्डः क<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> यन्त्रस्य विन्यासस्य "
"विषये सूचनां संग्रहीतुं प्रयुक्तम्<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</"
"link> . विभाजनसारणीनां भिन्नाः प्रकाराः सन्ति, प्रत्येकस्य स्वकीयाः सीमाः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:223
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sometimes also referred to as <quote>disk label</quote>."
msgstr "कदाचित् <quote>डिस्क लेबल</quote> इति अपि उच्यते ।"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:230
#, no-c-format
msgid "Primary Partition"
msgstr "प्राथमिक विभाजन"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:232
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A <link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">partition</link> directly inside a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">partition table</link>, as opposed "
"to <link linkend=\"glossary-logicalpartition\">logical partitions</link>, "
"which are in <link linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition\">extended "
"partitions</link>."
msgstr ""
"एकः<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनम्</link> साक्षात् अन्तः a<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\"> विभाजनसारणी</link> , इति विरुद्धम्<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"> तार्किकविभाजनम्</link> , ये इषु "
"भवन्ति<link linkend=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"> विस्तारितानि विभाजनानि</"
"link> ."

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:235
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">Partition tables</link> usually "
"impose restrictions on the maximum number of primary partitions that can be "
"created on a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. For MS-DOS "
"type partition tables, for example, this maximum number is four."
msgstr ""
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partitiontable\">विभाजनसारणी</link> प्रायः "
"प्राथमिकविभाजनस्य अधिकतमसङ्ख्यायां प्रतिबन्धान् आरोपयन्ति यत् a<link linkend="
"\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> . MS-DOS प्रकारस्य विभाजनसारणीनां कृते, "
"उदाहरणार्थं, एषा अधिकतमा संख्या चत्वारि अस्ति ।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-extendedpartition\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-logicalpartition\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"शब्दकोश-विस्तारितविभाजनम्\"></glossseealso> "
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"शब्दकोश-तार्किकविभाजनम्\"></glossseealso>"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sector"
msgstr "क्षेत्र"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:246
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A unit used to divide up a <link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-partition\">Partitions</link> must always begin and "
"end on a sector."
msgstr ""
"विभक्तुं प्रयुक्तं एककं क<link linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> .<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-partition\"> विभाजनानि</link> सर्वदा एकस्मिन् क्षेत्रे आरम्भः "
"समाप्तिः च भवितुमर्हति।"

#. Tag: glossdef
#: glossary.docbook:248
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso>"
msgstr ""
"<glossseealso otherterm=\"glossary-head\"></glossseealso> <glossseealso "
"otherterm=\"glossary-cylinder\"></glossseealso> इति"

#. Tag: glossterm
#: glossary.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid "Sector Size"
msgstr "क्षेत्र आकार"

#. Tag: para
#: glossary.docbook:257
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The number of bytes per <link linkend=\"glossary-sector\">sector</link> on a "
"<link linkend=\"glossary-device\">device</link>. The sector size of most "
"devices in use today is 512 bytes."
msgstr ""
"प्रति बाइट्-सङ्ख्या<link linkend=\"glossary-sector\"> क्षेत्रम्</link> on a<link "
"linkend=\"glossary-device\"> उपकरणम्‌</link> . अद्यत्वे प्रयुक्तानां अधिकांशयन्त्राणां "
"सेक्टर् आकारः ५१२ बाइट् अस्ति ।"
